Before moving on, it's useful to learn about a very important concept available in browsers: LocalStorage LocalStorage is a useful way to store strings in the browser as a key-value pair This type of web storage can be manipulated by JavaScript to manage data in the browser LocalStorage does not expire, while SessionStorage, another kind of web storage, is cleared when the browser is closed The various types of storage have pros and cons to their usage Note - your browser extension has its own local storage; the main browser window is a different instance and behaves separately

